---
// src/pages/privacy.astro
import PolicyLayout from '../layouts/PolicyLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../data/site';
---

<PolicyLayout
  title="Privacy Policy - Cyber Alliance India | Built with Intent"
  description="This policy explains how we handle your data when you visit our website."
  badge="Legal Documentation"
  heading="Privacy"
  highlight="Policy."
  lastUpdated="December 30, 2025"
>
  <p>
    Welcome to <strong>Cyber Alliance India</strong> ("we," "us," or "our"). We are committed to
    protecting your personal information and your right to privacy. This policy explains how we
    handle your data when you visit our website.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>We only collect the minimum amount of data necessary to provide our engineering and IT services.</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Information You Provide to Us:</strong> We collect names and email addresses only when
      you voluntarily submit them through our Web3 Forms (e.g., contact forms or inquiries).
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Payment Information:</strong> Payments are processed via <strong>Cashfree</strong>. We
      do not store your credit card or bank details on our servers. Cashfree collects your payment
      information directly to process the transaction.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Automated Information:</strong> We use <strong>Umami Analytics</strong> to collect
      non-identifiable technical data (such as browser type and pages visited). Umami is a
      privacy-focused tool that does not track you across other websites or use "tracking cookies."
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. Our Tech Stack & Third-Party Providers</h2>
  <p>
    To run this website efficiently, we use several third-party services. Each may process data
    according to their own privacy policies:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Infrastructure:</strong> Hosted via Cloudflare (Security/CDN) and GitHub (Source code
      storage).
    </li>
    <li><strong>Domains:</strong> Registered through Gandi.net and Dynadot.</li>
    <li>
      <strong>Communication:</strong> We use Chatwoot for our live chat plugin. Information shared
      in chat is stored to help us assist you.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Navigation & Media:</strong> We use Google Maps (embedded) and YouTube (video
      hosting). These services may collect your IP address or use cookies if you interact with the
      map or video player.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Utilities:</strong> We use Dub.co for URL shortening and Web3 Forms for form
      processing.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Business Communication:</strong> We use Zoho Mail for secure email hosting and
      WhatsApp (Business API/App) for direct customer communication.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
  <p>We use your data for the following "specified purposes" as per Indian law:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>To respond to your inquiries submitted via mail, forms, or chat.</li>
    <li>To process payments for services via Cashfree.</li>
    <li>To analyze website traffic (anonymously) to improve user experience.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Legal Basis (India DPDP Act 2023)</h2>
  <p>
    By using this site and voluntarily providing your data (filling out a form or starting a chat),
    you give your <strong>clear affirmative consent</strong> for us to process that data for the
    intended purpose. You may withdraw this consent at any time by contacting us.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Data Retention & Security</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Retention:</strong> We keep your name and email only as long as necessary to fulfill
      the purpose of your request or as required by law (e.g., tax records for payments).
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Security:</strong> Our site is served over HTTPS via Cloudflare. While we take
      reasonable steps to protect your data, no method of transmission over the internet is 100%
      secure.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
  <p>Under the Digital Personal Data Protection Act (DPDPA), you have the right to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Request a summary of the personal data we hold about you.</li>
    <li>Request correction or erasure of your data.</li>
    <li>Withdraw your consent for data processing.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>7. Contact Us & Grievance Redressal</h2>
  <p>
    If you have questions about this policy or wish to exercise your data rights, please contact our
    Grievance Officer:
  </p>
  <p class="mb-0 text-sm">
    Email: <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`} class="text-blue-500">{SITE.email}</a>
  </p>
</PolicyLayout>
